.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\[en]tree\f[R]
Show the repository as a directory tree.
.TP
\f[B]\-l\f[R], \f[B]\[en]long\f[R]
Show profile, HOME path, type and file size for each entry.
.TP
\f[B]\[en]source\f[R]
Show repository source paths instead of HOME paths.
.TP
\f[B]\[en]less\f[R]
View the output in an interactive pager (uses \f[CR]$PAGER\f[R] or
\f[CR]less \-RFX\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\[en]export\f[R] \f[I]<FILE>\f[R]
Export the effective managed files as logical HOME\-relative paths.
With \f[CR]\-\-profile\f[R], exports that profile\[cq]s paths instead.
.TP
\f[B]\[en]import\f[R] \f[I]<FILE>\f[R]
Import a previously exported JSON file and create symlinks using the
current active profile.
Correct links and regular\-file conflicts are preserved; files without
an effective source are reported as warnings.
Older exports containing \f[CR]common/\f[R] or
\f[CR]profiles/<name>/\f[R] paths remain supported.
.PP
\f[B]Export JSON format:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
{
  \[dq]version\[dq]: 1,
  \[dq]files\[dq]: [
    \[dq].bashrc\[dq],
    \[dq].config/starship.toml\[dq],
    \[dq].config/nvim/init.lua\[dq]
  ]
}
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Notes:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]FILEPATH\f[R] is always the HOME path, for example
\f[CR]\[ti]/.bashrc\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]no profile\f[R] means the source file is stored in
\f[CR]common/\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Commands that manipulate files should use the logical path:
\f[CR]tildr restore .bashrc\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Use \f[CR]\-\-profile\f[R] to target a variant explicitly:
\f[CR]tildr restore .bashrc \-\-profile linux\f[R],
\f[CR]tildr del .bashrc \-\-profile no\-profile\f[R], or
\f[CR]tildr cat .bashrc \-\-profile linux\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Use \f[CR]tildr list \-\-source\f[R] to inspect all repository source
paths
.IP \[bu] 2
Use \f[CR]tildr source\-path <file>\f[R] to inspect the repository
source path for one file
.IP \[bu] 2
Export files always contain logical paths and never expose the storage
hierarchy
.IP \[bu] 2
Tree view prints the managed HOME path tree
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR].tildrignore\f[R] patterns and internally excluded files are not
shown
.IP \[bu] 2
Export creates a portable snapshot of managed files for use on other
machines
.IP \[bu] 2
Import creates parent directories in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] as needed and
skips files already correctly linked
.SS tildr source\-path
